text: Orange County is a county of Vermont in the United States. At the 2020 census, 29,277 people lived there. Its shire town (county seat) is the town of Chelsea. It was created on 2 February 1781. == References == Category:18th- century establishments in Vermont Category:1781 establishments in North America Category:Vermont counties Category:1780s establishments in the United States
